Created attachment 28321
input test file

when the color of an svg generated oval is the same as the color of a preceding inline text, the svg oval is mis-colored (black); however, if the color of the oval differs from the color of a preceding inline text, the svg is colored correctly;

Created attachment 28346
patch file

the attached patch fixes this bug; the problem was use of setColor() versus updateColor(): the former did not update the PDFPaintingState, while the latter does; note that PDFImageHandlerGraphics2D already used updateColor() while PDFImageHandlerSVG erroneously used setColor();
